Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 300 degrees. Thinly slice the
@button mushrooms{8%ounce}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel,
and mince the @shallot{1}. Strip the @thyme{1/4%ounce} off the sprigs, then
roughly chop the leaves. Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Slice half the
@polenta{1} into ½-inch thick slices (save the rest for another day!).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Once hot, sear the polenta for about ~{1%minute} per side, until golden
brown. Transfer to a #baking sheet{} and place in the oven to keep warm.

In the same pan, heat @butter{1%tablespoon} over medium-high heat. Add the
mushrooms to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{5-6%minutes}, until golden brown.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the
shallot, thyme, and garlic to the pan and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until
softened. Add ½ cup water and the @veggie stock concentrate{1} to the pan.
Bring the ragout to a boil, then reduce to a simmer until reduced and thickened
for ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove the pan from heat, then stir in the
@sour cream{2%ounce} and mushrooms. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Toss the @arugula{2%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} with @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon}
and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Plate the crispy polenta cakes and top with the mushroom ragout and a sprinkle
of @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and parsley. Serve the tangy arugula salad to the
side and enjoy!